{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, as such tools enter creative domains, they prompt inquiries regarding whether and to what extent such tools can meet human creativity across several settings (Stevenson et al., 2022).",
    "As GenAI has the potential to significantly alter knowledge and creative work, this article uses two complementary perspectives to explore the multifaceted opportunities and challenges of GenAI for knowledge and creative work and the implications for future IS research.",
    "Knowledge and creative work share many similarities.",
    "For example, creative workers require an understanding of various forms of knowledge (Loo, 2017), and creativity is a distinctive and dominant feature of knowledge work (Frenkel et al. 1995), which also entails many creative processes.",
    "We explore how GenAI transforms knowledge work in terms of four organizational capabilities: knowledge creation, knowledge retrieval, knowledge sharing, and knowledge application."
  ]
}